-- Silver Lake shelves bid for Shutterfly, Snapfish - Bloomberg
-- 
-- Fri Oct 10, 2014 05:55PM EDT
-- None



Oct 10 (Reuters) - Private equity firm Silver Lake failed to reach a deal to acquire and combine photo-sharing sites Shutterfly Inc <SFLY.O> and Snapfish by a deadline of Friday, Bloomberg reported, citing people familiar with the matter.

Silver Lake was in advanced talks to acquire Shutterfly for at least $2 billion, Reuters reported last month. [ID:nL6N0RN3UE] Bloomberg reported that Silver Lake is still open to returning to talks with Shutterfly. (http://bloom.bg/112ccVZ)